London Henry Maynard
th
Sr. in answer to yd of 28: pas., I have writ the needfull to ur coots att bruges about the
goods to come with remingls of which exspect the invoyces p next: Iobserve rekond
theex tohye of the mony payd mr. baudier, where fore pray lett itt be altered according
to what you note y for I have not yett carried itt over inclosed the acctt. of sale of yt
which please to exmine & finding wright noto accordingly all acctt. of 81 will be veady
att yd coming god willing, I could wish to see you here, before you settle anyting
att brussels about laces, for & supose I can do some thing to yd advantidge more
then yett you know att least must brussels be yd way before this Ican meet
you there to come then hether: Iam ust going for brussels now in hopes
to finde more mony there to remitt you which shall follow I hope p next
post: & doubt wee shall have warr, because there is some news of the pancurs
haveing arrested all french goods in all spaine which if be true will
certainly breake outt the wwarr & carry as away first, intrim wee must
leave all to providence whilst you may be sure of my endeavour forge
intrest & horrest

S in answer to yd of 12:curitt you have don amis totell smy gould without my
orden, because itt was to loose when yett wort you that afterthes rate noted
itt would not loose, for rather the to have lost one nemme should have sent
othir spetie & disposed of the gold otherwise when yd assigne comes itt shall
finde due honour inducatons to have no more of yd contradit tory lines
though yett &exspect yd abatement as for the bayes of ƒ29 sende them
to mee according toye promise Ill exspect them, butt they must be here by
friday att furthest to serve my turne, so de depend therupo & if you
an, abato any thing pray doitt & que mee yd sadaise & sorh remainne

London Edmund warnerf
Sr. my last to you was on the 12: curitt seice non from you, so this onely to carry the
inclosed invoyce of the 2 packette of laces acctt to £260:19:2 which is the full of
yd order except one. of crawats with duble purkes of about ƒ 15 which I could not
finde to content , these breng little non made that are worth that price att
present I have added onep of without ground because others do often order such sorts
I can not aprehend anj the bast faurth should be in this percelt therefore desire
you to examin the whole & give mee yd oninion, for laces can not be cheaper
I am surg non is served upon better termes, so you iust not undervalew
them butt well make them worth the great risco & intrest & to content
you have here also inclosed yd acctt. curett the ballance of which I have
this day drawne on you payable att 2 uso to the order of mr. Henry maynard
for the valew of mr. Cornelis ande wiel beeng £265:1 t att 35:4 which is thevere
hileft of theex. so desire you please to give my bill due honour & in what
occasion elce you shall please to command, mee you may be sure of my
endeavour to promote yd intrest as my owne & remaine 17 xb 1681
london Henry maynarel
Sr. my last to you was rathe 12: curitt sence have understand that John ceminge wad
att the road of osfend, so hope he is gott in att bruges before now this is the
last letter I shall write tto you blfore yd commny away &hope he shall
reach yd handes: Iam desine for a freind to draw, on m. Erniund warnen
£265:11: st which I remitt you on him att 35:4 att 2 uso for yd accttbeeng
£468:8„2 which though be noted for the valew of Cornelis van dewill
must be noted as desire, & that & supfose is proforme a wordin answerof
dittom. warner because smight more oftend remitt you on him &
soremaine with kinde salutte
